Revision history for Daemonise

1.28    2012-10-31T14:24:12
        fixed "uninitialized value" warnings, added account to log() output

1.27    2012-10-23T02:16:32
        rewrite of RabbitMQ plugin, requires massive changes

1.26    2012-09-18T00:10:12
        fixed bug in JobQueue log()

1.25    2012-09-17T13:45:42
        added start_job() method to Jobqueue plugin

1.24    2012-09-17T12:27:51
        2 new plugins Event and Redis implementing lock/unlock methods and
        creating of events via couchdb or rabbitmq plugin

1.23    2012-09-10T18:55:23
        new plugin HipChat providing a notify() method

1.22    2012-08-01T19:17:34
        don't log worker more than once in JobQueue plugin

1.21    2012-06-22T15:34:52
        [FIXED] confessing makes daemonize rabbits die, don't confess, carp and return

1.20    2012-06-14T18:01:41
        [CHANGED] made find_job() more generic and simple, requires view renaming

1.19    2012-05-05T15:07:34
        [FIXED] use random channel number to not block same channels to often

1.18    2012-03-21T17:47:14
        [CHANGED] return existing job if duplicate found

1.17    2012-03-21T14:04:53
        [FIXED] find_job() by_transaction_id only needs the id and no platform
        as all callbacks come in via iwantmyname.com

1.16    2012-03-05T19:09:13
        [FIXED] sort keys with dumper before md5 hashing over it to make it
        actually work...

1.15    2012-03-05T19:09:13
        [FIXED] _id NOT id when calling put_doc() FFS!!!

1.14    2012-03-05T18:18:37
        [FIXED] only manipulate $msg after checking if job exists

1.13    2012-03-05T18:18:37
        [FIXED] no need to update job with job ID in meta data

1.12    2012-03-05T18:01:23
        [CHANGED] introduced duplicatejob detection by hashing over input
                  data + 2 min. caching timestamp

1.11    2012-02-21T11:09:13
        [NEW] implemented log_worker() for convenience

1.10    2012-02-20T22:17:24
        [CHANGED] last_update => updated

1.9     2012-01-12T18:46:52
        less printing if debug is off

